      "description": "Available is a 2003 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated M96 flat-six. This unit is paired with the desirable G96 6-speed manual transaxle, offering crisp gear synchronization and a mechanical shift feel. Significant preventative maintenance has been addressed, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS) to ensure long-term reliability. The suspension retains its factory-spec geometry with MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup, providing excellent turn-in and high-speed stability. Braking performance is anchored by four-piston Brembo monobloc calipers over vented, cross-drilled rotors. The exterior and interior show minor patina consistent with a well-loved driver, but the powertrain and chassis remain tight and responsive, delivering a visceral, analog performance profile.",
